@page
@model HowItWorksModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "How this works";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p class="lead">
    A stock <code>dotnet new webapp</code> Razor Pages app, running on Vercel as a container.
</p>

<p>
    The only Vercel-specific piece is a <code>Dockerfile.vercel</code> at the repo root.
    Vercel builds it on every commit and runs the image on Fluid compute, which autoscales
    and scales to zero when idle. The container just needs to serve HTTP on the
    <code>PORT</code> Vercel provides &mdash; <code>Program.cs</code> binds
    <code>http://0.0.0.0:$PORT</code>, and TLS is handled at the edge.
</p>

<p>
    See it all in the <a href="https://github.com/bennor/dotnet-on-vercel" target="_blank" rel="noopener">source on GitHub</a>,
    or read the Vercel docs on
    <a href="https://vercel.com/kb/guide/does-vercel-support-docker-deployments" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Docker deployments</a>.
</p>
